Subject: [ghostium] Navigator language / languages hook

Spec-E wiring. Anchors at top of ``navigator_language.cc``. The real
calls into ``FingerprintNoiseSource::PrimaryLanguageOverride`` and
``LanguagesOverride`` land inside ``NavigatorLanguage::language()``
and ``NavigatorLanguage::languages()`` respectively.

This complements (does not replace) the ``Accept-Language`` header
handling, which the WebContents-level UA override (Spec-C
``EmulationBridge``) already drives via ``UserAgentMetadata``. The
Blink-exposed ``navigator.language(s)`` hook is needed because the
header-side override does not feed those getters in every renderer
configuration.

